openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  contact:
    x-twitter: microsoft
  description: The Video Search API lets you search on Bing for video that are relevant to
    the user's search query, for insights about a video or for videos that are
    trending based on search requests made by others. This section provides
    technical details about the query parameters and headers that you use to
    request videos and the JSON response objects that contain them. For examples
    that show how to make requests, see [Searching the Web for
    Videos](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cognitive-services/bing-video-search/search-the-web).
  title: Video Search Client
  version: "1.0"
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - cloud
  x-logo:
    url: https://twitter.com/microsoft/profile_image?size=original
  x-origin:
    - format: swagger
      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/master/specification/cognitiveservices/data-plane/VideoSearch/stable/v1.0/VideoSearch.json
      version: "2.0"
  x-providerName: microsoft.com
  x-serviceName: cognitiveservices-VideoSearch
  x-tags:
    - Microsoft

  - apiKeyHeader: []

            example, if the second request has a different flight assignment

            the client ID to tailor web results to that client IDâ€™s search
            history, providing a richer experience for the user. Bing also uses
            this header to help improve result rankings by analyzing the
            activity generated by a client ID. The relevance improvements help
            with better quality of results delivered by Bing APIs and in turn
            enables higher click-through rates for the API consumer. IMPORTANT:

          required: false
          x-ms-client-name: TextFormat
          x-ms-enum:
            modelAsString: false
            name: TextFormat
          schema:
            type: string
            enum:
              - Raw

        "200":
          description: Success.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VideoDetails"
              examples:
                Successful video detail:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Successful_video_detail"
        default:
          description: An error has occurred. Check the response type and/or status code

          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse"

        Videos](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cognitive-services/bing-video-search/search-the-web).
